<!--***********************************************************
*  Example 3:  Using "newNamespace" within a section
*  to reuse existing variable names.
************************************************************-->


<p>The next three sections demonstrate the use of "newNamespace"
within the <tag>section</tag><tag>/section</tag>component.  In the first two sections, a single variable name for a text input is used to 
refer to the same user-supplied value.  In the third section, 
"newNamespace" is invoked within the section component in order
to reuse the same variable name but for a new user input value.</p>

<section><title>Play "Name that Alien!"</title>
    <p>Let's say you are a sci-fi author building a new universe.  What
    name would you give to your alien character?</p>
    <image width="100" source="" />
    <textInput name="alien_1"></textInput>
    <p>Welcome, $alien_1 to planet Earth!</p>
</section>

<section><title>Play "Getting to know $alien_1..."</title>
    <p>What is $alien_1 's favorite food?</p>
    <textInput name="food"></textInput>
    <p>Let's bring a peace offering to $alien_1 of $food...</p>
</section>


<section newNamespace><title>Play "Second Round"</title>
  <p>In this section, notice how the same textInput name="alien_1" is used again for a different name</p>
  <p>What name would you give to your new alien character?</p>
    <image width="100" source="" />
    <textInput name="alien_1"></textInput>
    <p>Why hello there, $alien_1!</p>
</section>



